# Cloudflare Pages may 302 /page.html → /page (“pretty URLs”). That breaks auth ?return= which
# expects real paths like /locker.html. Do NOT add /path → /path.html 200 rewrites for app pages:
# Pages can also redirect /path.html → /path, which ping-pongs with that rule → ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS.
#
# Use real .html paths in links (e.g. /locker.html, /store.html, /games.html). pilot-auth normalizes
# extensionless paths in ?return= (lantern-pilot-auth.js).
#
# Login: do NOT add /login → /login.html 301. Same ping-pong risk. Use /login.html only in links.
# Admin: no /admin → /admin.html 301 here. Use /admin.html in links.
#
# Locker, store, games, teacher, explore: no extensionless ↔ .html redirect rules here (same ping-pong).
#
# change-password: no /change-password → .html 301. Use /change-password.html in links.

# Root: serve index.html (client redirects to /login.html). Do NOT rewrite / → login.html.
